“Steve and Jonathan are just kids! You can’t hold them accountable…” 
“Funny, Billy is also 17.”
“17 is an adult! He knew better!”
“So we need to hold the other boys to the same standard, right?”
“No, they’re just babies!”

The progeny produced from this branch of the family disappeared without a trace around the time of the Oblivion Crisis as the Thalmor overthrew the rightful heirs to the throne. Will a member of this line be the hero of Elder Scrolls VI? Only time will tell! 16/16
She may not be a Princess, and her husband may only be #264th in line to the throne, but Gilly is at last satisfied to be a Duchess with faithful Arox by her side. 15/?

Calling in the favour to end all favours from Queen Ayrenn, Astarlis gives Gilly the title of Lady Ravenwatch and sends her to the Summerset Isles and the Aldmeri Court. Gilly wastes no time procuring a worthy suitor, a handsome yet awkward young Duke. 14/?

A master with blades, Gilly is the only child that showed an interest in physical combat, and she excelled at it. However, all she ever wanted, all she ever wanted was to be a real princess, just like everyone told her she was. 13/?

Gilly is Astarlis’s doppelgänger in appearance, and her name roughly translates to “Champion of All the Stars.” From a young age, she developed a fondness for Arox the Mutilator, bedazzling him with ribbons and bows at every opportunity. 12/?

Finally, we have everyone’s favourite Daedrat-loving little princess, Giliathdacil (Gilly). She is loud, boisterous, and practically came out of the womb with the mindset to always get what she wants. 11/? https://t.co/1D8tNq0I4J

Baz is introduced to a distant Tharn relation, who becomes her traveling companion and later romantic partner. The pair have children, family grows, and slowly they migrate back to the Imperial Court. This results in the birth of the one-day Hero of Daggerfall. 10/?

With her elder brother making a life for himself in Cyrodiil, Baz is gifted the title of Lady Mathiisen from her mother, learns the ways of the Psijic Order, and even assists the Mages Guild in hunts for rare texts on occasion. 9/?

This became Astarlis’s favourite book, and it inspired the name for her eldest daughter. Baz is an incredibly curious and intelligent li’l mer, and her magical aptitude rivals that of her parents. Thankfully, she did not inherit Revus’s Dangerprone Daphne status. 8/?

Next up is Ahrtabaza (Baz), the middle child and oldest twin (by about 5 minutes). After Astarlis went to Summerset and dealt w/ the Court of Bedlam, she stayed at the Crystal Tower, studying the libraries. She read  “The Faerie Chain” by Ahrtabazus. 7/? https://t.co/EmDggaXHLW

Mirilir and Nephelle travel, procuring unique furniture pieces and crafting materials for their own avant-garde artwork. Eventually, they end up in the Imperial Court in Cyrodiil and climb the social ladder on their talents and the reputation of Mirilir’s famous family ties. 5/?

Mirilir is a sweet, kind-hearted boy who inherited his father’s disposition and his mother’s love of crafting. He’s not much for adventuring, but he enjoys hunting for and studying antiquities across Tamriel with his parents. 3/?

While Azura stole the golden hue of the Chimer’s skin and left it the colour of ash, Alandro Sul wandered amongst the Ashlanders, shrieking into the hot winds of Red Mountain against the evils done to him and his beloved Nerevar by that traitorous Tribunal.

Alandro Sul found himself alone though he cried out for mercy from Azura. However, her attention had turned towards punitive measures against the Chimer for the betrayal and murder of Nerevar at the hands of Vivec, Sotha Sil, and Almalexia.

By the beginning of the First Era, the Chimer were beset with dissidents from outside and from within, culminating in the Battles of Red Mountain. Before Nerevar could slay Wulfharth Ash-King, leader of the invading Nords, Alandro Sul fell to a mighty Thu’um that blinded him.

With Azura focused on him, those false memories were strong, spurring him forth. Alandro Sul, touting to be a son of Azura, quickly became Nerevar’s companion and both lover and rival to Vivec with each vying for Nerevar’s attention.

Azura chose Amaure for this task as he was more malleable than his sister, more eager for praise and power, despite Y’ffre’s decree. With magicka-forged memories and donning the golden skin of a Chimer, Amaure was placed in Nerevar’s path with the name Alandro Sul.

This would not stand for Azura’s next plot. For a time, the Prince of Dusk and Dawn let her playthings sleep, distracting herself with the affairs of the Khajiit and the Altmer. Keen to sense an opportunity for more devoted followers, Azura eased her way into the hearts of the…

I’m nervous about posting all that, but it feels good to finally begin to tell my OC’s tale in detail. 💗

And so it was. Azura could transform the twins with a word between any race of man or mer, but they would never be her beloved Khajiit, and they would always hold her in the greatest contempt for her treachery against their true mother, Nirni.

Y’ffre crafted a tale so quickly that Azura could not close the veil between Oblivion and Nirn before he was finished. He spoke thusly, “Here is the bitter truth for one so filled with vanity and spite. Change their forms all you will, but you will never have their love.”

Their ferocity split the Ooze, creating twins where there once was one — Astarlis, the dusk, and Amaure, the dawn. Azura’s will proved too great, and she pulled the pair into her realm of Moonshadow. However, Y’ffre would have the last word as he was so clever with them. https://t.co/EZMAUiihat

Y’ffre spun a story that caused the forest people to take shape as the Bosmer, yet Azura held tight to the prize she so desired. Viciously, Azura and Y’ffre fought— Azura selfishly, and Y’ffre for the sake of Nirni’s broken heart. https://t.co/Z8FRFGzTbN

Azura saved one special bit of Ooze for last, one that was both male and female, wicked and virtuous. This one Azura planned to keep by her side for all eternity as her champion of beauty. Y’ffre, song-spinner and tale-teller, realized Azura’s deception, & stopped her.

Azura, Prince of Dusk & Dawn, went to her sister, Nirni, and offered to help make the forest people the most beautiful. However, Azura did not plan to make them more like mer; she instead made them into the Khajiit, cats of many unique shapes.

To tell Astarlis’s story is to go back, waaaay back when the stars were new, and Nirni had spawned the forest people, the Bosmer. Nirni was heartbroken because the Bosmer could not hold their shape, transforming between mer and beast. Astarlis was one of these first Bosmer. https://t.co/hEs8Q6reXE

26. Astarlis is the height of fashion, designing and creating her own jewelry and clothes. She will always dress to suit the locale or the occasion. She uses so much purple dye though. https://t.co/WituZWnfm8

25.5 Astarlis is just tired, and her power wanes as Azura’s strength fades. She cannot protect Nirn forever, and there’s a part of her that no longer wants to. If it wasn’t for Farkas and her kids, she might have given up entirely. Let’s see what ESVI holds for her.

25. Astarlis just wanted to find out who she really was. In the 2nd Era, she had hope, energy, and a zest for life. By the 5th Era, she knows the truth of her past, yet it brings her no peace. She sees man & mer undo all the work she did to protect Nirn and unite Tamriel.

24. Astarlis was probably most recognizable during the 2nd Era/ESO. By the late 3rd Era, her name would be lost to time as she slumbered in Moonshadow. Her later reincarnations have their own infamy in their own times, but all will eventually fade into legend.

17.) Astarlis has innate magical abilities. She always has to relearn to use them after every reincarnation until her memories and instincts kick in. She’s quite proud of her illusion skills, always helpful to sneak about.

16.) Azura holds power over Astarlis’s grip on Nirn and can easily snatch her back to Moonshadow (at least until 4E). If Astarlis does finally shuffle off the mortal coil, she hopes Dibella will intervene to save her soul from Daedric clutches, like Molag Bal’s.

15.) Astarlis’s favourite work of fiction is Feyfolken by Waughin Jarth, but her favourite book of all is The Faerie Chain by Ahrtabazus. She loves the book so much that she named her first daughter Ahrtabaza.

“Red Diamond” is Astarlis’s favourite song (particularly the version sung by male bards aka Crispin Freeman). I really associate Astarlis and her reincarnations with Regina Spektor’s “Us.”
https://t.co/VSND1xdHuv
13.) Astarlis is a “think-on-the-run” mer. However, she probably does lean more toward action, which does not always work out well. https://t.co/id5cP5SFQD

12.) Astarlis’s sign is the Atronach, which is fitting given that she technically is one, having been constructed by Azura from the primordial ooze from which all Bosmer sprang. If it wasn’t for Y’ffre, Astarlis would have lived her life as a mortal Khajiit.

11.) Astarlis bought Ald Velothi Harbor House to be close to Revus. She carefully decorated it to suit both their tastes, including creating a beautiful study and egg hatchery. She loved sitting there for hours just listening to Revus chat absently as he scribbled his notes.

I like to think of Astarlis as the Ultimate Mary-Sue — An adorable yet powerful hero, beloved by all, who makes cakes and jewelry in her spare time… and who, by the 4th Era, is literally just one bad day away from burning all of Tamriel down.

10.) I think Astarlis has always tried to redirect the attentions of the Dark Brotherhood and the Thieves Guild to more positive activities… but there’s only so much you can do with the whole Black Sacrament thing. Also, don’t get me started on the Bards College. https://t.co/iL6MgLwQRj
9.) At this point, Astarlis has belonged to almost every guild and society in Tamriel. She’s even been the leader of many. Her favourite role has been that of a Nightingale. It’s that sexy armor.

8.5) Astarlis has a twin brother, Amaure, who she doesn’t know exists, and Azura plans to keep it that way. Amaure is the HoK, and the twins did meet during Skyrim while he was in the guise of Sheogorath.

8.) Astarlis has been close to all her children (from Rev: Mirilir, Ahrtabaza, & Giliathdacil; adopted: Sofie & Runa Fairshield; from Farkas: Wren). However, she has only met 1 descendant in her reincarnations, and that was Baladas. https://t.co/AR7FEzbw9p

7.5) Romance: During 2E, Astarlis married Revus Demnevanni. It was love-at-first-rescue. During Skyrim, she married Farkas before she gained her memories back. For the future, I think she may end up with Verandis Ravenwatch since he can relate to the pain of such a long life. https://t.co/UBnAbHnsM2

7.) Friends/Companions: The members of the Moonstone Trading Co. (Phineas Arbourbloom, Sings-to-Hatchlings, etc.) are her dear friends during 2E along with Mirri and Bastian. Astarlis is also close to Razum-dar.

6.) Astarlis has been both a vampire and a werewolf (during the events of Skyrim). She has met enough people to know that the curses are not always a willing choice, & she wouldn’t attack someone just for being one. She prefers not to be cursed & will seek a cure for herself. https://t.co/m7dqWV45CE

5.) It is probably a good thing that Astarlis was not the HoK because if she was the one to shoulder Sheogorath’s mantle and unleashed even a fraction of her repressed rage, Nirn would have been in for some dark days.

4.) Astarlis’s backstory is fairly lore-friendly except that Azura and Meridia are pulling more strings than canonically stated. Also, Astarlis becomes less DragonBORN than DragonMADE (through Daedric nonsense). Azura has a DIY approach to prophecy https://t.co/xQ9AFJEiai

3.) Astarlis is the Savior of All Nirn. Though she has often been placed in the path of events beyond her control, she answers when she is called… aka Astarlis doesn’t start fights, but, by Dibella’s ample bosom, she will finish them.

2.) Astarlis awoke in Coldharbour with no memories because she has none. Azura planted her in Mannimarco’s path after eons of keeping her in stasis in Moonshadow. The Prophet saw her as the special chosen one, and Astarlis just accepted it… just like Azura planned. https://t.co/fmkovxLmGm
